                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                     <seg type="para">This fragment consists of the upper portions of
                                four torn folios from a bilingual Greek-Arabic Gospel lectionary,
                                probably copied in the 11th century. The presentation of the text in
                                both Greek and Arabic would suggest that it was produced for a
                                Christian community in the Levant, one which had become
                                predominantly Arabic-speaking but retained Greek as a liturgical
                                language.</seg>
                            <seg type="para">A much larger portion of this manuscript is now <bibl subtype="external" type="MS">St Petersburg, Rossijskaja
                                    Nacional'naja biblioteka, MS gr. 84</bibl>, of 41 folios, which
                                includes the lower parts of these torn folios.</seg>
                            <seg type="para">Dr Christopher Wright</seg>
                        </summary>

                        <textLang mainLang="grc" otherLangs="ar">Greek and Arabic</textLang>

                        <msItem n="1">
                            <title xml:lang="eng">Gospel lectionary</title>
                            <note>Gregory-Aland <hi rend="italic">l</hi> 311; Scrivener Eust.
                                297</note>
                            <note>Parallel text in Greek and Arabic</note>
                            <note>The Greek text of the fragment begins during the (<hi rend="italic">synaxarion</hi>) lection for the fifth Sunday of
                                Luke (Lk 16:24) and ends during that the 6th Sunday of Luke (Lk
                                8:30), with multiple lacunas due to the loss of the lower part of
                                all folios.</note>
                            <incipit defective="true">
                        <locus from="1r" to="1r">f. 1r</locus> ὅτι
                                ὀδυνῶμαι ἐν τῆι φλογὶ ταύτη</incipit>
                            <explicit defective="true">
                        <locus from="4v" to="4v">f. 4v</locus> καὶ
                                    ἀπῆλ<supplied reason="damage">θεν καθ’ ὅλην</supplied> τὴν
                                    πό<supplied reason="damage">λιν κηρύσσων</supplied> ὅσα
                                    ἐπ<supplied reason="damage">οίησεν αὐτῷ ὁ</supplied>
                                Ἰησοῦς.</explicit>
                        </msItem>
                    </msContents>

